Branch
Decreasing anisotropy
Shuyao Kong
2020-02-02

Try decreasing anisotropy from AnisStart = 0.8 all the way down to AnisEnd = 0.2
Let anisotropy at height 0 be AnisStart and anisotropy at height frontArrHeightIni be (AnisStart+AnisEnd)/2, and let anisotropy decrease linearly with height (minimum is AnisEnd)

Values tried:
AnisStart = 0.8, 0.6, 0.4
AnisEnd = 0.2, 0.1, 0.0

Finally, the values 
AnisStart = 0.6
AnisEnd = 0.1
are determined to produce the shape most similar to a WT plant sepal